  "text": "Low-stringency single specific primer technique represents a simple repetition of PCR process with one of the two primers used in the initial amplification by creating low-stringency. Serovars of Leptospira were analyzed by G1 and G2 primers that led to differentiation of Leptospira species [CITATION_1] . Discrimination of serogroups of Leptospira from different animal reservoirs and clinical suspicion of leptospirosis were studied using LSSP-PCR [CITATION_2] .",
